    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nAs I've noted [here](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/18393#issuecomment-1907827221), `string.format` does not support positional arguments, whereas `vim.fn.printf` does. This is an issue when an argument `N` must be re-used many times in a format string; `string.format` just doesn't cut it.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nAdd `vim.format` that would support everything `vim.fn.printf` is capable of.",
    "closed_at": "2024-01-24T10:54:22Z",
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I don't think that's a compelling argument for adding yet another API. `vim.fn.*` _is_ part of the Lua API, so that would just be filling empty checkboxes for no perceivable practical gain. Native Lua APIs are added when there is a significant demonstrable benefit in performance (avoiding marshaling non-native types) or flexibility (composability of other Lua APIs such as LSP or treesitter). None of those apply here, as far as I can tell.\r\n",
